January 13, 2026
SENATE BILL No. 211
_____
DIGEST OF SB 211 (Updated January 12, 2026 11:49 am - DI 149)
Citations Affected: IC 3-13.
Synopsis: Cancellation of caucus meeting. Allows a person who
wishes to be a candidate for a pro tempore appointment to certain local
offices or school board offices to file a declaration of candidacy with
the chair of the caucus or the circuit court clerk. Allows a notice of a
caucus meeting to be rescinded if only one candidate seeks to fill a
vacancy in a local office or a school board office held by a major party.
Effective: July 1, 2026.
Holdman
January 8, 2026, read first time and referred to Committee on Elections.
January 12, 2026, amended, reported favorably — Do Pass.
