13 JULY 1, 2026]: Sec. 10. (a) Except as provided in subsection (c), the
14 members of a caucus held under this chapter shall select, by a majority
15 vote of those casting a vote for a candidate, a person to fill the vacancy
16 described in the written notice of the caucus.
17 (b) If more than one (1) person seeks to fill the vacancy, the
18 selection shall be conducted by secret ballot.
19 (c) The following apply if only one (1) person seeks to fill the
20 vacancy:
21 (1) The notice for a caucus sent under section 4 of this chapter
22 may be rescinded and the caucus is not required to meet.
23 (1) (2) A vote under subsection (a) is not required.
24 (2) (3) The county chairman may select that person to fill the
25 vacancy.
